Older park with playground, sports fields, and two half-court basketball courts. This facility also has a lighted Rugby field. For the 1st 2 years of my stay I was pretty happy with how things were going I will say maintenance is on top of getting things fixed when requested the amenities in the building are awesome but ther are definitely some downsides to living here 1st I will discuss how management does little to make sure residents are happy my personal storage in the building was broken into last year and it took them four days to change the Broken lock to my storage Because I didn't have a police report yet never were they apologetic or caring that $1500 worth the bikes were stolen from my storage I let that go...recently after living here for 3 years and requesting a parking space in my own building from day one and was told there was no available spaces and no waiting list I watched 3 people in my hallway including someone I referred to the apartment get spaces in my building And after explaining to them the safety concerns of having to cross a major driveway with no stop signs with my 3 kids and almost being hit on numerous occasion they inform me that there were 2 spaces available and that they would submit it for approval and I could use the spaced until approved after 3 weeks I was told that I wasn't approved Because I received a discounted rate when I moved in and saved $30 after explaining to them that actually the $30 I saved the 1st year They added to my remt increase the 2nd year making my rent increase a $150 the 2nd year I moved and a $120 each  Following year They then told me that it was out of their hands.... after contacting Avalon Bay customer service I was told it is actually up to the  Management at the building.When I contacted management again they then told me that the parking spot was previously given away to a tenant on floor 3  And that I would be put on a waiting list. < Review>
Daniel is a great person of contact, we moved from out of state and he was able to handle everything remotely without an issue. The complex is beautiful and is very pet friendly with a little fenced in area for dogs to run freely right on the side of the property. There is security patrolling the area, but I am concerned with the ease of non residents being able to access the facilities. There is a gate at the front of the complex but it remains open long enough for cars to tag along behind you. The pool and workout areas are accessed with a keyfob but I've seen other residents open the gate/doors for strangers who ask to get in. We've been here for about three weeks and I've seen the security guard several times throughout the day, which puts me at ease. It still makes me uneasy about these people potentially breaking into my mailbox, I wish those were more secure or had obvious security cameras.

But the complex is gorgeous and modern with nice utilities and a friendly staff.<//Review>

<Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
Avalon WH is a good place to live if you work in the area.
What is good: Nice location with stores like Ralphs and Target within walking distance.Amenities like a dedicated dog park,a basic but clean gym and two nice pools + jacuzzis with barbecue areas.Management in the leasing office is responsive and helpful

The bad:Theft from mailboxes and tresspasing by homeless people is on the rise.Dog owners dont pick after their pets business.Coyotes roam the hills on the back of the property.Lighting is sketchy in corridors and common areas.

The ugly: Smell of weed is all pervasive throughout this property. Internal walkways and aisles have people smoking/vaping.Shady people in the east pool area during afternoons and the east exit gate.

Updated review 3/25/2017
I am updating the review since a lot has changed since I posted.We have since moved out but the move out experience was great.
Also there is now round the clock 24hr security that checks on all areas.Haphazard Parking in the internal streets has stopped because the parking agent asks you to move.Mailboxes have new locks and cameras.Smoking smell/weed smells have almost dissappeared maybe because of the cameras and screening for residents.The back of the property is now fenced off.
Much better property now than when we moved in.< /Review>

< Review>
I have never actually submitted one of these in the past, but my experience with the folks at this shop was do dreadful, infuriating, and demeaning that I was compelled to say something.

Upon, arriving I was initially told that I would need to get on a queue, despite the fact that they did not ask or let me finish stating my purpose at their location. Once my turn came, a brief 10 minutes later, I managed to explain my case to the assigned agent. Since my inquiry was about a damaged phone, they asked if I had insurance and promptly placed me in front of an ipad to file a claim online. While the process might seem intuitive, it is a bit limiting if you as hamstrung by the lack of a phone as you will need a phone number or access to email to complete the verification. This meant I had to hunt down a third agent, who stopped me half way through my explanation in order to "hook me up" with a phone to call customer support. This process only cycled back to the need for verification via a email or a text, which was yet again impossible as I did not have a functional device. This mean I had to hunt down a fourth agent, to ask about other options, to my delight he briskly responded that they are a "dealership" and as such do not bother with providing customer support and urged me to try again, then proceeded to focus on his mobile device and ignore me.

Such poor manners on behalf of all four agents who provided customer "service". I really is a pity that AT&T has shifted all support services to remote centers and that the provided support mechanism is an oroboros of frustration aided by nonchalant employees who simply can't be bothered. Glossy shop,  devoid of humans.</Review>

<gmapID>0x8085900804de31f7:0x2ca9fe456b128d47< /gmapID><time>1608741352287</time><rate>5< /rate>< review>
I really cannot say enough good things about Paul and his team. I have been going here for 3 years now with 2 different cars and several big issues. Paul is honest, forthcoming, resourceful, and trustworthy. He looks to offer you multiple solutions when possible so you can choose what is right for you, your car, and your bank account. He will refer you back to the dealer or a specialist if he thinks they are better suited for a job because he wants your long term business and understand a that trust is a huge part of that. As an individual, Paul gives back to his community, lives a life of generosity, and wants to protect you. I never get mad about having to take my car in for a scheduled oil change or if the check engine light goes on because I love seeing Paul and know it will be an easy process working with this team. While I don't get to interact with the whole team often it is clear that these values go beyond just Paul. If this wasn't enough to convince you to give Mill Valley Auto a shot, they also text message updates and prompts for scheduled maintenance. You can communicate with Paul at any time on text! While that is simple, it's a huge help when you are stuck in meetings all day and can't call.<//review>

<resp>None</resp>< text>
Jerry and Paul are some of the very friendliest people in the industry that I have ever had the privilege to meet.

Having just gotten a puncture flat late in the afternoon short distance away, I called MVAS to inquire about their service and availability, and Jerry said that he'd fit me in.

No surprise but the most pleasant of one when I rolled in. Jerry and Paul where there to welcome me and then they immediately went to work  patching the flat.

Thorough as well I must add. After re-installing the wheel with the patch repair, they checked the air pressure on the other three tires, the spare, and even re-installed the full sized spare to he undercarriage of my truck. All this in just under an hour!

I was able to get on with my work day as if nothing happened, and will gladly give them my truck repair and maintenance needs in the future!

Thank you!

<UserId.>104565901182968868756</UserId.><text>It's been a few months since my experience with Paul and Mill Valley Auto Service (MVAS). I'm sorry if anyone missed out because of the delay in my review!

My car broke down in Mill Valley. After leaving it overnight in a commuter lot, I nursed it the half-mile to MVAS on a Sunday and left it at their door. Throughout the next week I was in contact with Paul (and John), who worked hard to fix my car at a price that I could afford. Long story short, years of outdoor east coast life have rusted a lot of the underside of my car. The critical components are there, but as Paul made clear, "every time you have work done, there will be additional costs for materials and workarounds." I needed a lot of extra stuff, and he got it to me all at a discount. I'm pretty sure I only paid for the service and major components, but the front axle he managed to scrounge for me was free. I got the car back and I was pleased. Paul took the time to put my car on the lift and show me what he'd done. He reassured me that my car still had life left and was safe to drive.

Over the next week I noticed a noise coming from a front wheel well - I'm pretty convinced that this was caused by driving my broken car the half mile to MVAS. I brought it back (just in case) and after taking a test ride with one of Paul's employees, I had a bearing replaced. Turns out that wasn't the bad bearing; when I got the car back for the second time, it was still making the noise! They ended up replacing the other bearing for free, and did some work on my brakes as well for my trouble.

I had a fantastic experience with MVAS. It was a lot of back-and-forth, but in the end it was so worth it for the patient, honest, and fair service. When you take your car to MVAS, you will be treated like family. Everyone is friendly and helpful and will take the time to explain to you the condition of your car, the work that needs to be done, and the costs of that work. Paul, MVAS, thank you for everything you've done for me and my car.</text></record>

<review>I'm rather surprised at the negative reviews, but who knows.  I will say this; we had a minor disaster and these guys stood behind everything, made everything MORE than right. and bent over backwards to make sure everything was perfect.

So, I cannot speak of selection, or some less than perfect customer service interaction, but these guys stood behind their work and went the extra mile, and more.

We ordered new lens for my daughters ancient frames; the frames were 8 years old, but she loved them did not want to change.  Installing the lenses, they broke the frame because the plastic was very old; they really should have said "no" to the attempt, so the lab manager agreed to give us a free frame of comparable price, plus lenses to fit the new frame shape we pick out.

Daughter, crushed and hopeless, could not find a frame she liked, and could not really even see well enough to shop frames.  The manager put the new lenses in some temporary frame just so my daughter could shop, and then when we found frames that were much more expensive than the original, the manager agreed to just give them to us.  He then prepared new lenses on the spot to fit the new frames, AND ordered a pair of the more expensive lenses to fit the new frames.

I hope the long story makes sense, but bottom line; I recommend highly on the basis of protection and satisfaction with the end result.  There are downsides to going with a national chain, but there can be advantages too.

< review>
I have been going to them for about 5 years, and have been going to eye doctors for over 20 years total (so some experience with trying different places). I knew this place was different because I was treated very well by the doctor, and the doctor made every effort to explain what he was seeing and what I should do to maintain my eye health. This continued for several years of seeing different doctors at this practice. I've seen both Dr. Shapiro and Dr. Kitamori several times and have really liked both of them, but every Doc I've seen there over the years has treated me well and given me excellent information.

At one point, I tried switching away from them because they're not very close to my house anymore, but it was a disaster. That doctor talked down to me and wouldn't explain what was going on with my chronically dry eyes other than reacting immediately to the fact that I hadn't walked in with sunglasses. I think she was so used to speaking with pediatric patients that I was unfortunately talked down to on that same level. Never again! I brought my business right back to this UTC office and have never looked back.

This office is also super easy to schedule with online, and they seem to innovate regularly, which is cool too.< /review>

< review>
This place really stands behind its name Rock & Wings ü§òüé∏ Based on wings I have tryed around town, this place has one of the bestüëå really tasty and big wings. The beer is super cold like its supposed to be. The service was good but pricing is a bit high compared to competitors. They do have weekday specials. The atmosphere is really cool and rock pictures and art is all over including a drum set on the sealing. They got enough seating for this size place and lots of parking. It also has a pool table in the back that is a little tight but manageable. They do have karaoke which is always fun üé§. Overall this place is really cool and recommended.<//review>

<user_id>101929615338806701165</user_id>< username>
LaToya Mitchell<//username>
< time>
1532451596456<//time>
<Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
We were really impressed with this place. The theme is rock...classic rock, alternative rock, etc. The atmosphere was great, welcoming & really cool to look at all the rock related art on the walls, ceiling, tables & behind the bar. We ordered the Original wings & Lemon Pepper wings with Rockin Tots. The food was delicious & the wings are good size. Our waitress, Jazmin, was very attentive,  knew every kind of beer they carried by heart, and had great customer service. The beer is served in chilled, clear glass mugs that literally have ice on them...so incredibly refreshing & delicious!
I really enjoyed the rock music playing, the gigantic screen TV playing a sports channel & 2 other TV's showing rock concerts.
As much as I enjoyed the place, this is somewhere I would go with just the hubby & leave the kids at home, so we could re ally enjoy it but it's not a bad place to take kids. The waitresses arent dressed skimpy either, which makes taking the kids ok, but still present a good level of attractiveness (if that's what your looking for).
My only con, which did not reflect on my rating bc it was a small issue, was the room temp. It was cooler than outside but still kinda warm. I get hot when I have a beer so buy the time I was eating I was a tad sweaty. Overall, my hubby & I loved this place & will definitely return. We recommend trying Rock & Wings out. They do to-go orders also!< /Review>

< Review>
Great environment especially if you love rock.
However if you spend on the touchtunes employees will skip over songs , has happened numerous times for me. So I wouldn't reccomend spending on the music. Food is good If you dine inside. Do not order to go, employees always get the order wrong & wings are always over cooked, & dried out. I gave this business multiple tries and due to bad service & bad food on the to go side, I will have to make it the last time I give my money to this establishment.
Please hire people who are able to take orders over the phone correctly & please explain to the cooks to stop over frying the wings! It's well worth the wait if my order is correct & cooked correctly!<//Review>

<UserId.>113921605404899083234</UserId.><user_name>Brenda Yaneth<//user_name><date>1555305544841</date><Rate>5</Rate>< text>
I was there for the first time this past Saturday and I loved, LOVED this place. Great service, great food & amazing music. We had the regular wings 1/2 buffalo sauce & 1/2 honey chipotle (both just perfect but I think the Chipotle was my favorite), a side salad & the Light My Fire Sandwich <-- You have to try this! I didn't think we could find steak "alambre" anywhere in Bakersfield but I'm glad we did. The meat was so tender and flavorful, they should make it in street tacos (if they don't already). As a plus, I love that they play both Spanish and English Rock and they literally have posters/pictures of my favorite Rock En Espa√±ol bands. I think I've seen them all live. It made me feel sorry I didn't wear a band t-shirt to go eat there lol. Can't wait to go back!</text>

This place was a huge disappointment. We went on the recommendation of a co-worker. It was decorated in an interesting way, but the music was so loud  we couldn't hear to order. Once we did place our order it took a long time to receive. Even our waitress was suprised we were still waiting. We got the food to go, and when we got home it was mostly inedible. 3 different flavors and they were all bad.  Bbq was tasteless, like no taste at all. Teriyaki tasted like they burned the wings and then just doused it in sauce. And the lemon pepper was so heavily seasoned it was like eating just pure seasoning. We spent over $20 and barely ate any of it.</Text>

101565214997418151691< /userid>
<username>L< /username><date>1509303727837<//date>< rating>
4</rating>
< Text>
I was curious about the opening of this coffee, wine, and beer spot. Being as fixated as I am, I thought "meh, let me stop by and see what the fuss is about". I will give this place 5 starts because as any new place, there are things you won't know until you open your door to customers and wait for the feedback. Here are a few points, good and otherwise. First, I would welcome a greeting when people walk in, or perhaps a sign that reads "please seat yourself, if you require assistance please let a staff member know" I.e., handicap necessities and what not. Second, as I experienced, if it is custom to order from the bar, have a sign that states that so people are not waiting at their table or standing, waiting to order. The food was delicious and the beer/coffee?...amazing! Just a few suggestions, I hope it helps.

Now my second time at this brewery and they still haven't made the signs any clearer which should  state that you should order at the bar. I would highly recommend something more visible because people seems to walk right by the sign outside and the sign at the bar is tiny and I only noticed because I happened to be staring at the lights. The amount of food you receive isn't that great, I would recommend a bit bigger portion sizes for the price.< /Text>

<user_id>114663226038442440637</user_id><name>Carlie Regan<//name><date>1529560409051</date><Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
The best thing to come to Diamond Springs in a while. A really comfortable and delicious local gem! The acoustics can be loud and overwhelming on a busy night, but they're working on it. The beer and wine selection is fantastic, as they say boldly in their bio, the co-owners have experience and truly know what they are doing. I'm so grateful to have a local place that shows talent in brewing more than just IPA's, they have created incredible lagers, ales, sours, stouts and more. Chef Shane will blow you away with his culinary creations (say yes to ghost pepper cheese). Portions are smaller for the prices, though still delicious.<//Review>

<user>103999825952536998501<//user><pics>None< /pics>< time>
1528564438289< /time>
<text>Stumbled on in on Friday after having a doozy next door at Allez.  To my surprise, the customer traffic was outstanding.  It made the drinking experience more memorable than it probably was.  Service was great.  The bartenders are there to help, they were friendly, and were the best part about my visit.
The beer was not terrible by any means, but I wouldn't drink it regularly.  I grew up on Saison's, and I don't think the offerings at Solid Ground were any better than average.  In my opinion, the downfall was somewhere in the yeast.  The IPA's were ok.  The Trango is on the Milkshake IPA side and it was loaded with fruit, not much hops.  Again, not my preference.  The Clouds Rest tasted like a West Coast NE IPA if that makes sense to beer snobs.  It was good at first, but the appeal was lost after about 6 oz.
Overall, very happy I was able to check this brewery off the list.  They have great ambition, a wide range of styles, and don't compromise with providing a beautiful location to grab a decent beer.< /text>< rate>
3< /rate>
